
Revert Command in Git:
  It purpose of modify the local data and remote area data and it will not modify the commit history but it will create new revert commit history

  Steps to create revert commit
    Step 1: use git log (to take the histoty of commands)
    Step 2: select current commit id present in the history and copy the id 
    step 3: create the revert commit using git revert paste the id 
    step 4: generate the new revit commit and press enter

